&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48190540</guid><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 08:03:50 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: Viberia – Civ/Polytopia-like command center for AI agents (BYOK/BYOS)</title><link>https://getviberia.com/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hey HN,&lt;p&gt;This is my take on the agent harness. Everything on an isometric map. Agents are grouped into "buildings" that run in a sequence or a loop; e.g., the CodeForge has an agent that writes a PRD, another one that implements, and a third that reviews. Everything is customizable, you build your own buildings/teams however you want.&lt;p&gt;It's a Tauri app, really light (about 8x less energy than the closest competitor I benchmarked, so it actually runs from a coffee shop on battery). It's macOS only for now, but ping me if you are willing to test the Windows or Linux version.&lt;p&gt;I've been dogfooding this for months and would love to get some feedback, feature requests, and bug reports so I know what to focus on next.&lt;/p&gt;
